  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed alterations to the front elevation and roof extension to the rear of the main roof slope, by reason of their appearance, design, massing and width, would go against the established pattern of development along the Lowfield Road street scene and would be out of keeping with the local roofscape. It would also be visually insubordinate to the building's original roof to the detriment of the visual amenity provided by the local built environment. As such, the proposal is considered contrary to section 12 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2019), as well as, Policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021); 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013); and Ealing's Supplementary Planning Document 4 - Residential Extensions. | The proposed development, by reason of inadequate GIA and undersized bedrooms would provide substandard accommodation to the detriment of the living conditions of future occupiers contrary to policies 3.5, 7B and 7D of the Development Management DPD (2013), Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021), The Technical Housing Standards and the National Planning Policy Framework (2018)."
  ],
